  "prompt": "What is an interface icon?",
  "response": "An interface icon is a graphical representation used in user interfaces (UI) to denote actions, functions, or content within a software application, website, or operating system. Icons are designed to be intuitive and recognizable, allowing users to quickly understand the purpose of a function without needing extensive text explanations. \n\nFor example, a trash can icon typically represents the action of deleting files, while a magnifying glass icon is commonly used for search functions. Interface icons help streamline user interaction and improve the overall usability of software by enabling faster navigation and reducing cognitive load. Icons are often accompanied by tooltips or labels for clarification, especially if the icon's meaning might not be immediately clear to all users.",
